==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Impluvium
<hw>Im*plu"vi*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr.
<ets>impluere</ets> to rain into; pref. <ets>im-</ets> in +
<ets>pluere</ets> to rain.]</ety> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>In Roman
dwellings, a cistern or tank, set in the atrium or peristyle to receive
the water from the roof, by means of the <xex>compluvium</xex>;
generally made ornamental with flowers and works of art around its
brim.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

